      "message": "The failures on 10/13 - 10/14 morning have mix reasons. \n1) The comparison operation is heavy and the version was wrong. It overrode 100% traffic to Go instead of 10% (I uploaded my local version for the convenience of some manual testings and didn\u0027t realize the dispatch.yaml had taken effect in Dev). I noticed it spun up 124 instances - https://screenshot.googleplex.com/5WXCgYayx6FeWoR.\n\n2) Majority requests have the permission issues which we discussed in the meeting. Their responses are like `rpc error code \u003dnot found`. But the service didn\u0027t attach the appstatus code and as a result, it became the internal error. It has been fixed in the parent CL.\n\n\nNow, Dev has run the correct version over 10+ hours and everything looks good. So I decide to turn on verification in Prod. I\u0027m going to monitor it and if any issues, I\u0027ll roll back to the non-overridden version.",
